<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-288] User Guide bugs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-288</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Draft reviewing is my 3rd job after java coding and open source coding, so figured I&amp;#39;d submit the grumbles about the groovy-user guide&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These are all pretty simple, so merging them into the one bug:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;General: Could do with next-previous links at bottom of page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Statements: equivlanent typo&lt;br/&gt;
Statements: &apos;1.1. Important Note Note&apos; looks like it is lacking markup&lt;br/&gt;
Statements:  &lt;/p&gt;
{link:GroovyBeans|beans.html}
&lt;p&gt; looks like it didn&apos;t copy over from Wiki well&lt;br/&gt;
Statements:  &apos;Expando&apos; is a bit magic and not explained. A comment in the source example would be useful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Strings: Could do with explanation as to whether all Strings are GStrings, or if they have to be specially created. An example needed if all Strings are not GStrings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Collections: implemenation typo&lt;br/&gt;
Collections: increment/decrement are not Comparable methods. Where do they come from?&lt;br/&gt;
Collections: Needs example of subscripting on a Map/Regex&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logical branching: Provide link to Groovy class that needs extending to provide own Matcher for switch statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looping: Lack of a Map example for a &apos;for&apos; loop. It&apos;s needed as it either is, or could be expected to be, different to the others.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Classes: Need example of a class for first section. &lt;br/&gt;
Classes: Bad indentation on the UseFoo example.&lt;br/&gt;
Classes: The last example needs a better name than foo. It&apos;s the first time the reader has met the idea of pushing a value onto a list using a bit-shift operator, so a better name would save having to explain this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Java differences:  &apos;Use then&apos; typo.&lt;br/&gt;
Java differences: &lt;/p&gt;
{link:closures|closures.html}
&lt;p&gt; links failed to come over from Wiki&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regex: This page is not linked from the user-guide contents. Seems a better fit to the user guide than the &apos;Features&apos; section.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
